President Biden has declared an emergency in the state of South Carolina due to the conditions resulting from Hurricane Idalia. The declaration authorizes the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to save lives and protect property and public health. FEMA is authorized to mobilize equipment and resources to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. Emergency protective measures will be provided in all counties in South Carolina. Brian F. Schiller of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.